SIMPLE: chromatophore
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chromatophore
<hw>Chro"ma*to*phore`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/,
<?/, color + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A contractile cell or vesicle containing liquid
pigment and capable of changing its form or size, thus causing changes
of color in the translucent skin of such animals as possess them. They
are highly developed and numerous in the cephalopods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of the granules of protoplasm,
which in mass give color to the part of the plant containing
them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chromatoscope</ent>⟦br⟧
